      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): add Authorization header to provider preflight probe",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nReplaced the hand-rolled Authorization header logic in the cron preflight probe with the shared `resolveProviderRequestHeaders()` from `provider-request-config.ts`. This ensures the preflight and normal model request paths build identical auth headers for the same config.\n\n## Changes\n\n### P1: Reuse shared auth normalization (ClawSweeper finding)\n\n- **model-preflight.runtime.ts**: Replaced the manual `if (params.apiKey) { headers[\"Authorization\"] = ... }` / custom-header construction with delegation to `resolveProviderRequestHeaders()` via `sanitizeConfiguredProviderRequest()`\n- Auth is now resolved through the same code path as normal model requests — any future changes to auth formatting apply automatically\n- Full credential chain preserved: `request.auth` override → `resolveApiKeyForProvider` fallback → no auth\n\n### P0: Error redaction at cache-write time\n\n- **model-preflight.runtime.ts**: Applied `formatErrorMessage()` to errors before storing in `preflightCache`, preventing unredacted error objects from remaining in heap between cache write and read\n\n### P0: Header prefix trimming consistency\n\n- Prefix is now trimmed via shared `sanitizeConfiguredProviderRequest`, matching the behavior of `resolveAuthOverride` in the normal request path\n\n### P2: Cross-path auth header parity tests\n\n- **model-preflight.runtime.test.ts**: Added 4 parity tests (P0) verifying preflight and normal path produce identical auth headers for the same config\n- Added 4 edge case tests (P1): empty header fields, unknown mode, whitespace token, OAuth marker filtering\n- Total: 31 tests pass (was 23)\n\n## Files Changed\n\n| File | Δ |\n|------|---|\n| `src/cron/isolated-agent/model-preflight.runtime.ts` | +99/-40 |\n| `src/cron/isolated-agent/model-preflight.runtime.test.ts` | +413/-3 |\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** Cron job preflight was building custom auth headers (`request.auth.mode === \"header\"`) with hand-rolled logic that missed prefix trimming, header collision cleanup, and `request.headers` merging — inconsistent with the shared auth normalization used by normal model requests.\n\n**Real environment tested:**\n- **OS:** Windows 11\n- **Runtime:** Node.js v24.14.0\n- **Branch:** fix/cron-preflight-clean at d0f8be2fdf\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n```bash\npnpm vitest run src/cron/isolated-agent/model-preflight.runtime.test.ts\npnpm vitest run src/agents/provider-request-config.test.ts\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:** Terminal output captured after running the tests:\n```\n ✓ src/cron/isolated-agent/model-preflight.runtime.test.ts (31 tests) 564ms\n ✓ src/agents/provider-request-config.test.ts (30 tests) 62ms\nAll 61 tests pass across both files. No regressions.\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** All 31 preflight tests pass, all 30 provider-request-config regression tests pass. Code review confirmed: no Critical or Important issues, auth delegation is correct with proper fallback semantics and edge case handling. Test engineer confirms: thorough coverage at correct mock boundaries.\n\n**What was not tested:**\n- Integration test with actual local provider endpoint (preflight tests mock `fetchWithSsrFGuard`)\n- `prepareProviderRuntimeAuth` plugin auth exchange path (documented gap — preflight intentionally skips this for local provider probes)\n",
        "branch": "fix/cron-preflight-clean",
